# Root-level .dockerignore used by builds whose build context is the
# repository root (client, server). Per-workspace .dockerignore files
# (client/.dockerignore, server/.dockerignore, prisma/.dockerignore,
# common/.dockerignore) are NOT consulted when the context is higher up,
# so all exclusions for multi-module builds must live here.
#
# Exclude every workspace's installed dependency tree. This is critical:
# on Windows the host's node_modules contains junction points whose
# resolved target is a Windows path (e.g. C:/Users/.../prisma). BuildKit
# preserves these as Linux symlinks pointing at the same absolute Windows
# path, which does not exist inside the Linux container. Yarn then
# refuses to overwrite the already-present (broken) symlinks during
# `yarn install`, leaving `node_modules/@local/prisma` and
# `node_modules/@prisma/client` pointing nowhere - which causes TSC to
# fail with `Cannot find module '@prisma/client'`.
**/node_modules

# Build outputs
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo

# Yarn local state (keep yarn.lock; exclude cache + ephemeral state)
**/.yarn/cache
**/.yarn/install-state.gz
**/.yarn/build-state.yml

# Logs and coverage
**/*.log
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output
**/tsc.log

# Editor / VCS
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.vscode
.idea
*.swp

# Docs and misc repo-level artifacts not needed at build time
docs
README.md
LICENSE.txt
*.md
!server/README.md
!client/README.md
!common/README.md
!prisma/README.md

# Local env files that should never leak into images. The Dockerfiles
# explicitly COPY the .env files they need.
.env
.env.secrets
.env.secrets.example

# Docker-related files not consumed by app builds
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml
Dockerfile
**/Dockerfile
!client/Dockerfile
!server/Dockerfile
!prisma/Dockerfile
!common/Dockerfile
